1. create an account with github so that you can have a username and a email address
2. configure git settings
3. use command git config --global user.name (enter your github" username")
       	       git config --global user.email (enter your github email address)
4. Go to Github and create a repository and personal access token. Then copy the links to both the PAT and the repos
5. Clone your repo using command git clone (paste the links created above)
6. git add .
7. commit your repo with  messageusing the command git commit -m
8. git push
